### File 7: `pkg/controller/trustmanager/test_utils.go`

Update `testReconciler` to initialize the zero-value `proxyInformer` field (Applicable() == false):

No change needed — the `proxyInformer` field is a value type (`utils.OptionalInformer[...]`), not a pointer. Its zero value has `InformerFactory == nil`, so `Applicable()` returns `false`. The existing tests work without modification because:
- `testReconciler` creates a `Reconciler` struct literal that doesn't set `proxyInformer`
- The `getDeploymentObject` path checks `r.proxyInformer.Applicable()` before accessing the informer
- All existing tests will skip the proxy block since `Applicable()` returns `false`

